						<summary>

						<p>Hero-stone in front of the Karibasappa Temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">12th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This hero-stone has a sculptured panel depicting a hero fighting against a hero sitting on an elephant back. Probably the hero succeeded in killing both the elephant and the enemy on it. But at the end he succumbed to the wounds in the battle field. On top and bottom of the sculptured panel there are two panels containing writing, but damaged very much. It states that the hero probably Haṁniya died after piercing [the enemy and the elephant] to death.</p>						

						<p>It is in characters of 12th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
